I agree with [Mike&#39;s answer][1], but there&#39;s an implicit 3 second wait if no elements are found which can be switched on/off which is useful if you&#39;re performing this action a lot:

    driver.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(0, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS);
    boolean exists = driver.findElements( By.id(&quot;...&quot;) ).size() != 0
    driver.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(3, TimeUnit.SECONDS);

Putting that into a utility method should improve performance if you&#39;re running a lot of tests.

  [1]: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6521270/webdriver-check-if-an-element-exists/6521834#6521834

