If you have configured my logback-spring.xml as per Spring Boot Documentation, this might be a better solution.
Instead of calling the whole application.properties in your logback.xml file, you can refer to a specific property in the application.properties file like this:

    &lt;springProperty scope=&quot;context&quot; name=&quot;APP_TIMEZONE&quot; source=&quot;application.timezone&quot; /&gt;


Then you can use the springProperty like this: **${APP_TIMEZONE}**.
This way you can call a specific value in the application.properties file.

    &lt;Pattern&gt;
        %d{ISO8601,${APP_TIMEZONE}} [%thread] %-5level %logger{36} - %msg%n
    &lt;/Pattern&gt;

